columns.name: name
columns.description: The name of the IP set.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the entity.

columns.name: id
columns.description: A unique identifier for the IP set.

columns.name: scope
columns.description: Specifies the scope of the IP Set. Possible values are: 'REGIONAL' and 'CLOUDFRONT'.

columns.name: description
columns.description: A description of the IP set that helps with identification.

columns.name: ip_address_version
columns.description: Specifies the IP address type. Possible values are: 'IPV4' and 'IPV6'.

columns.name: lock_token
columns.description: A token used for optimistic locking.

columns.name: addresses
columns.description: An array of strings that specify one or more IP addresses or blocks of IP addresses in Classless Inter-Domain Routing (CIDR) notation.

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags associated with the resource.

columns.name: partition
columns.description: The AWS partition in which the resource is located (aws, aws-cn, or aws-us-gov).

columns.name: region
columns.description: The AWS Region in which the resource is located.

columns.name: account_id
columns.description: The AWS Account ID in which the resource is located.
